From 0d9fb5bd4d8ca6772ba1a72d89f273c7bf36dad8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 18:01:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate module attribute startup loop

Production telemetry after PYCORE_TYPES:PASS repeatedly sampled stub 0x39c
(PyUnicode_New) while groups 7, 13e, 13c, 12c, d5, and d4 alternated.  This
matches the module method installation loop: _add_methods_to_object creates a
method, interns its name, resolves the module attribute path, and updates the
module dictionary for every PyMethodDef entry.

Pin the exact ten-function inner path to type-init group 7.  The measured
linked bodies total 5,836 bytes.  Starting from the audited 83,980-byte group,
the predicted result is 89,816 bytes in the 90,112-byte slot, leaving 296
bytes.  The post-link residency verifier remains the hard authority for fit.
